Business Brief -- Omni Exploration Inc.:
   Lewex to Sell 64% Stake
   In Concern to Cairn Energy
Omni said the closing of the stock sale is subject to
certain conditions being discussed by Lewex and Cairn Energy
USA.
   In January 1991, Lewex signed a letter of intent with
Southern Petroleum Refining Co. to sell all its shares of
Omni to Southern Petroleum for $1.4 million, but the
agreement expired without a sale.
   Omni Exploration is an oil and gas production company in
Columbus, Ohio.